What insurance is appropriate for me?
Insurance for a car that protects the driver in the event of an accident. represents a considerable expense that depends on various factors such as age, condition, gender, length of possession of a driving licence, the type of vehicle to be insured or used, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the appropriate car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, you need to be clarified what we're talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured.
That commitment takes the form of an insurance contract stipulating that the insurance undertaking receives an agreed insured amount of a certain amount for taking responsibility for the payment of the damage in the event of an insured event.
The insurance premium is the cost of the insurance, which is determined by taking into account various factors such as age, condition, gender, length of possession of a driving licence, the type of vehicle that is insured or used, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so the more likely to be an accident, the higher the premium rate.
For this reason, both those over 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
In the same way, based on the checks, insurance companies concluded that people living in a marriage tend to have fewer crashes than single drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of the journeys and thus the likelihood of having an accident.
The rise in the frequency of rides increases the likelihood.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when setting the cost of premiums.
Therefore, the driver must study the situation well to choose the kind of insurance that best matches his policyholder's profile.
We will show here the most important variables for the selection of this or another type of insurance, which, in addition to the fact that they comply with the type of insured person, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of 25 experience different draws, such as little driving experience and short possession of a driving licence when they want to arrange insurance premiums at an affordable price.
While ideal for good coverage is insurance against all risks, there are also cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can choose insurance against all risks at a discount premium to obtain the insurance coverage of all risks, but at a more affordable price.
This type of contract would presuppose a client's contribution to the insurance claim.
"Part of the reimbursement of the insurance claim provided by the client will be determined in advance when determining the price of the premium, which will be the higher, the co-payment would be, explains Luis Noguera, senior head of First Europe in Spain, an online insurance intermediary.
Another option is insurance extended to other traffic participants by the client insuring against the damage caused to other persons, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, it would be insured against theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Recommendations.
If you are under the age of twenty-five, try to be attentive and avoid accidents as possible, as this will affect your bonus and make it possible to reduce your premiums in the future.
The bonus is a reduction in the basic rate held by the insurance company.
By contrast, malus is an increase in that basic rate.
"The Bonus and the malus will depend on the insurance company and its profit.
If the insurance company has had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonus," explains Noguera.
After crossing the twenty-five-year mark, it is easier for drivers to take out insurance, as the client's risk index is lowered by their experience.
For this reason, it is most recommended to take out insurance against all risks at a discount.
"Young people are usually unable to take advantage of the experience gained in advance when the crash is made, nor in the driving process," assures the director of a European company in Spain, adding that most of the crashes occur in the second year of proceedings, when the "fear of a newcomer" has already been overcome.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is better to take out insurance against all risks, if his economic situation so permits.
Families with children are considered by insurers to be the clientele with the lowest risk index and therefore their surcharge will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks at a discount premium (which could be €300) or a high bonus, insurance extended to other operators, starting from the third year after the purchase of the vehicle.
"Their driving is calmer and their purchaseability is higher, so they can afford the luxury of getting the highest discount," notes Luis Noguera.
Pensioners are advised to be insured against all risks with a premium discount (which is €150) or insurance extended to other participants in the operation if a high bonus has been achieved.
It has to be said that car insurance is something important not only because it protects the driver in the event of an accident, but also because it represents a considerable expense, which is a valid reason to study the possibilities of insurance that would suit us best in view of our personal personal situation.
